content: I do not have any personal preferences or biases. however, i suggest checking out the old library, which was built in the 1800s and inspired by the bodleian library in oxford. it has beautiful victorian gothic architecture and is now home to the university's institute of arab and islamic studies. another notable building is the reed hall, built in the late 1800s with beautiful landscaped gardens, which is currently used for events and conferences. additionally, the queens' building, which houses the university's business school, has a fascinating design that blends classical and modern features. these are just a few examples, but i recommend exploring all the historical buildings on campus if you have the time!
